# Documentation Update Checklist

Before completing any code changes, verify:

- [ ] API endpoints documented in `docs/API.md`
- [ ] API endpoints documented in `docs/openapi.yaml`
- [ ] Database schema documented in `docs/DATABASE.md`
- [ ] Data models documented in `docs/OBJECT_MODEL.md`
- [ ] Project structure documented in `docs/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md`
- [ ] Examples are accurate and up-to-date
- [ ] Error responses are documented
- [ ] Request/response formats match the code

## Validation

After updating documentation:
- Verify OpenAPI spec is valid (can be checked with swagger-cli)
- Ensure all code examples are syntactically correct
- Check that all referenced files/paths exist
- Verify consistency between API.md and openapi.yaml
